    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n5194" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κείρω</span></b> , fut. inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κερέειν</span>, aor. 1 <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔκερσα,
            κέρσε</span>, mid. part. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κειρόμενος</span>, ipf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κείροντο</span>, aor. inf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κείρασθαι</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">shear, shear off, cut down;</span>
          <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κόμην, δοῦρα, τένοντε,</span>
          <i><span class="en">Il. 23.146</span></i>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc"> Ω
            450</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 10.546</span></i>; then
          ‘consume,’ ‘waste,’ <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κτήματα, βίοτον</span>,
            <i><span class="en">Od. 2.312</span></i>, 143; fig., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μάχης ἐπὶ</span> (adv.) <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">μήδεα
            κείρει</span>, ‘cuts short,’ <i><span class="en">Il.
            15.467</span></i>; mid., <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">cut</span> off one's own hair (as an
          offering to the dead), <i><span class="en">Il. 23.46</span></i>,
            <i><span class="en">Od. 4.198</span></i>.</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
